title: Hawks, 'Hounds Split Night on the Pitch
text:
Hawks, 'Hounds Split Night on the Pitch 
By Zach Schneider October 7, 2015 Updated Oct 7, 2015 at 9:49 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- The Hermantown boys' and Duluth East girls' soccer teams registered wins on Wednesday night, meaning the two area rivals split a night of soccer at Ordean Stadium. 
The Duluth East girls' team first beat Hermantown 1-0 on a first half goal, meaning the Greyhounds have now won seven of their past eight games.
